passed": true}, "short_span_min_tokens": {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 109}, "passed": true}}, "text": "7. CHOU EN-LAI HINTS AT ACTION IF HONG KONG RIOTS RECUR\n\n\"You know we could cause plenty of trouble in Hong Kong easily, but don't want to,\" Communist China's Premier Chou En-lai told\n\nChou stated such riots menaced China's security. He added that Kuomintang \"gangsters\" could create more riots and that \"peaceful\" residents might then decide to resist.\n\nComment\n\nChou made these remarks following British rejection of Communist charges that Hong Kong authorities had been derelict in dealing with the riots.\n\nChou's statement that \"peaceful\" citizens might resist during any future disturbance constitutes a warning that pro-Communist organizations in Hong Kong might act in case of any future riots", "token_count": 109, "token_end_0based": 108, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "7 chou en-lai hints at action if hong kong riots recur you know we could cause plenty of trouble in hong kong easily but don't want to communist china's premier chou en-lai told chou stated such riots menaced china's security he added that kuomintang gangsters could create more riots and that peaceful residents might then decide to resist comment chou made these remarks following british rejection of communist charges that hong kong authorities had been derelict in dealing with the riots chou's statement that peaceful citizens might resist during any future disturbance constitutes a warning that pro-communist organizations in hong kong might act in case of any future riots", "unred_source_page": 9}
